---
title: Spacing
---

p.-text Use shorthand margin and padding utility classes to control spacing between elements.

h3 Notation
p.-text Spacing utility classes can be defined using the format <code>-{property}{sides}{size}</code>.
h4 {property}
ul.-text
  li <code>m</code> - use to apply <code>margin</code>
  li <code>p</code> - use to apply <code>padding</code>
h4 {sides}
ul.-text
  li <code>t</code> - use to apply <code>margin-top</code> or <code>padding-top</code>
  li <code>b</code> - use to apply <code>margin-bottom</code> or <code>padding-bottom</code>
  li <code>l</code> - use to apply <code>margin-left</code> or <code>padding-left</code>
  li <code>r</code> - use to apply <code>margin-right</code> or <code>padding-right</code>
  li <code>x</code> - use to apply <code>margin-left</code> and <code>margin-right</code> or <code>padding-left</code> and <code>padding-right</code>
  li <code>y</code> - use to apply <code>margin-top</code> and <code>margin-bottom</code> or <code>padding-top</code> and <code>padding-bottom</code>
  li blank - leave blank to apply <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to all 4 sides.
h4 {size}
ul.-text
  li <code>0</code> - use to eliminate existing <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> and set to <code>0</code>
  li <code>1</code> - use to set <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to <code>$base-unit</code>
  li <code>2</code> - use to set <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to <code>$base-unit * 2</code>
  li <code>3</code> - use to set <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to <code>$base-unit * 3</code>
  li <code>4</code> - use to set <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to <code>$base-unit * 4</code>
  li <code>5</code> - use to set <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to <code>$base-unit * 5</code>
  li <code>6</code> - use to set <code>margin</code> or <code>padding</code> to <code>$base-unit * 6</code>

h3 Examples
h4 Margins
p.-text
  | In this example, various margin classes have been applied to render margin
  | on all 4 sides of the pink squares. The margin can be visualized in blue.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-grid.-noGutter
      .-mr3(style="background:#E6F0FF;border:1px dashed #2973E3;align-self:flex-start;")
        .-m2(style="width:3rem;height:3rem;background:#F74F87;")
      .-mr3(style="background:#E6F0FF;border:1px dashed #2973E3;align-self:flex-start;")
        .-m4(style="width:3rem;height:3rem;background:#F74F87;")
      .-mr3(style="background:#E6F0FF;border:1px dashed #2973E3;align-self:flex-start;")
        .-m6(style="width:3rem;height:3rem;background:#F74F87;")
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="-m2"></div>
    <div class="-m4"></div>
    <div class="-m6"></div>
